Scott: Nadia Falah: Rebecca Kronk: Alissa Bovee Terry: Kristi Graves: Justine Pickarski: Margaret Au: Correspondence: kkelly44@uthsc.edu 5 2025 27 1 2025 197 5 498074 e63990 e63990 27 08 2025 01 10 2025 02 10 2025 02 10 2025 This study examined the data generated as part of a seven-session webinar series that focused on genetics care provision in the medically underserved, rural Appalachian region and examined how these services have adapted to challenging practice environments. Barriers and facilitators to care in our region were considered. Data included a baseline survey of registrants, transcripts of sessions, and feedback about sessions. We analyzed data with a sequential and concurrent mixed methods approach.
